I went there with people from work for lunch. It was for all of us our first experience at an Albanian restaurant and it did not disappoint. We shared the mozzarella plate as an appetizer and for the main course each of us got something from the grill section (highly recommend) and each item was fantastic. The service was top notch and there was warm bread served with butter on the house. At the end of the meal the owner offered coffee or cappuccino on the house too. The food from the grill was just perfect and there is no skimping on the portions. The mix platter is a meat lovers dream. I got the stuffed burger with dry meat and sausage( I cannot say or spell the Albanian names) and it was topped off with a yogurt sauce and was scrumptious.I definitely want to go back with my family.

Ok where do I begin. First of all, I am almost always disappointed with my orders on ubereats. I don’t give reviews because I was told if you have nothing nice to say don’t say it at all. After my experience at Çakor, I felt compelled for the third time to write a review. I ordered the mixed grill, spinach burek, and the hot antipasto combination. Ubereats said the restaurant was out of burek so I called and they weren’t. Long story short I ended up with 2 orangina and a burek for free not because the restaurant made a mistake but because I couldn’t order it on ubereats. I really wanted to love the food after this nice gesture, but I was skeptical. I’m pregnant and nothing satisfies me. I have really picky kids and both me and my kids enjoyed the food thoroughly. The mixed grill was succulent, every single peace of meat. The mushroom stuffed with crab, the shrimp was amazing. If I could give it more stars I would. Plz don’t change chefs. This was wonderful. I will definitely be back.

Wow, this place was amazing. Stopped here late night after visiting the botanical garden and it was popping at midnight. Music was blasting and women were singing Albanian tunes.  The service was great. Super attentive and friendly staff made you feel at home.  I've never had Albanian food so it was totally new and interesting to me. I had the pjelkvika (?) - kindof a sausage patty - and various other spiced meats. All delicious. They went well with the roasted peppers and huge half loaf of bread served before the entree.  I left very full and would def like to go back.
